{{Infobox protected area | name = Altındere Valley National Park | alt_name = ''Altındere Vadisi Milli Parkı'' | iucn_category = | photo = Altinderevalley.jpg | photo_alt = | photo_caption = A view of Altındere Valley. | photo_width = | map = Turkey | map_alt = | map_caption = | map_width = | relief = yes | label = Altındere Valley NP | label_position = bottom | mark = | marker_size = | location = [[Maçka]], [[Trabzon Province]], Turkey | nearest_city = | coordinates = {{coords|40|42|31.62|N|39|38|55.18|E|region:TR|display=inline, title}} | area = {{convert|4468|ha|abbr=on}} | designation = | authorized = | created = | established = {{start date|1987|09|09}} | designated = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_ref = | governing_body = [[Ministry of Forest and Water Management (Turkey)|Ministry of Forest and Water Management]] | administrator = | operator = | owner = | world_heritage_site = | website = {{URL|http://www.milliparklar.gov.tr/mp/altinderevadisi/index.htm}} | child = | embedded = }} '''Altındere Valley National Park''' ({{lang-tr|Altındere Vadisi Milli Parkı}})), established on September 9, 1987, is a [[national park]] in northeastern Turkey. The national park is located in [[Maçka]] district of [[Trabzon Province]].<ref name="mp"/>
It covers an area of {{convert|4468|ha|abbr=on}}.<ref name=mp/>
