The '''Indang–Mendez Road''' is a two-to-four lane, secondary road that connects the municipalities of [[Indang]] and [[Mendez, Cavite|Mendez]] in [[Cavite]],  [[Philippines]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dpwh.gov.ph/dpwh/2016%20DPWH%20ATLAS/Road%20Data%202016/cavite.htm|title=Cavite|website=www.dpwh.gov.ph|access-date=2018-01-09}}</ref>

The road is a component of the '''National Route 402 (N402)''' of the [[Philippine highway network]].

The road is mostly paved with asphalt, while some other parts are currently being widened with concrete.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dpwh.gov.ph/dpwh/sites/default/files/Region%2520IV-A.pdf|title=Department of Public Works and Highways|website=www.dpwh.gov.ph|language=en|access-date=2018-01-09}}</ref>

