==South America== The standard list for the major peaks of the Andes is the list of 6000m peaks as first compiled by John Biggar in 1996 and listed in his Andes guidebook.<ref>John Biggar: The Andes - A Guide for Climbers, {{ISBN|0-9536087-2-7}}</ref> This list currently stands at 102 peaks, with no known completers. *[[List of Ultras of South America]] *[[List of mountains in the Andes]]
