{{Infobox valley | name = | embed = | other_name = | photo = | photo_size = | photo_width = | photo_caption = | photo_alt = | map = South Orkney Islands | map_size = | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = | label = | label_position = | coordinates = {{coord|60|42|S|45|37|W|type:landmark|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | location =[[Signy Island]], [[South Orkney Islands]] | elevation = | elevation_m = | elevation_ft = | elevation_ref = | direction = | length = | width = | area = | depth = | type = | age = | boundaries = | topo = | towns = | traversed = | watercourses = | footnotes = }} '''Three Lakes Valley''' ({{coord|60|42|S|45|37|W|}}) is a low [[valley]] containing three freshwater lakes, extending from the vicinity of [[Elephant Flats]] northward to [[Stygian Cove]] on [[Signy Island]], in the [[South Orkney Islands]]. The three lakes, from north to south, are [[Heywood Lake]], [[Knob Lake]], and [[Pumphouse Lake]].
The valley was surveyed and given this descriptive name by the [[Falkland Islands Dependencies Survey]] (FIDS) in 1947.
{{usgs-gazetteer|id=15248|name=Three Lakes Valley}}
[[Category:Geography of the South Orkney Islands]]
{{SouthOrkneys-geo-stub}}

[[Ganja, Azerbaijan|Ganja]], a popular tourist destination in [[Azerbaijan]] is the second largest city of the country. The city is located 400-450 meters above the sea level, lies on the Ganja-Gazakh plain in the Kur-Araz lowland in the west of [[Azerbaijan]], 375 km away from [[Baku]]. It is situated at the north-eastern foothills of the [[Lesser Caucasus]] mountain ranges on the Ganjachay river. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganja-ih.gov.az/page/13.html|title=Location|last=|first=|date=|website=Executive Power of Ganja|archive-url=http://www.ganja-ih.gov.az/page/13.html|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/364/5/Gence|title=Location|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan - Ganja Regional Culture Office|language=|archive-url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/364/5/Gence|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref> Ganja offers a variety of tourist attractions, including its nature, historical sights, monuments, museums, theaters and other places.
== Historic buildings == {| class="wikitable" !Attraction !Period !Description !Picture !Citations |- |[[Chokak Hamam|Chokak bath]] |1606 |The [[Chokak Hamam|Chokak Bath]] is located near [[Juma Mosque, Ganja|Juma Mosque]] in [[Ganja, Azerbaijan|Ganja]]. It was built in 1606 based on the project by the architect Sheikh Bahaddin Mahammad Amil. Mixture of egg-white with clay-lime and red brick was used in the construction. It has a large and two small domes. |[[File:Old bath in Ganja.jpg|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2013/12/14/m%C9%99d%C9%99niyy%C9%99t/g%C9%99nc%C9%99nin-'%C3%A7%C3%B6k%C9%99k-hamam'%C4%B1.html|title=Chokak hamam in Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=GanjaNews.az|language=az|archive-url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2013/12/14/m%C9%99d%C9%99niyy%C9%99t/g%C9%99nc%C9%99nin-'%C3%A7%C3%B6k%C9%99k-hamam'%C4%B1.html|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://azertag.az/xeber/Gencedeki_CHokek_hamam_esasli_sekilde_temir_edilir-29349|title=Chokak hamam in Ganja is being renovated|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=2018-09-24|archive-url=https://azertag.az/xeber/Gencedeki_CHokek_hamam_esasli_sekilde_temir_edilir-29349|archive-date=2018-09-24|language=az}}</ref> |- |Shah Abbas Caravanserai |XVII century |The Caravanserai dates to the XVII century is located 100 meters away from the [[Juma Mosque, Ganja|Juma Mosque]]. It was built during the reign Shah Abbas by the architect Sheikh Bahaddin in the Oriental style. Traditional mixture of egg-white with clay-lime and red brick was used in the construction. The caravanserai features 54 rooms and 13 halls, space for pack animals. |[[File:Şah Abbas karvansarayı, Gəncə 001.jpg|frameless]] |<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://azertag.az/xeber/Azerbaycanda_yeddi_mohtesem_karvansara-1133691|title=7 caravanserais in Azerbaijan|last=|first=|date=|work=Azerbaijan State News Agency|access-date=2018-09-24|archive-url=https://azertag.az/xeber/Azerbaycanda_yeddi_mohtesem_karvansara-1133691|archive-date=2018-09-24|language=az}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/monview/361/251/Sah-Abbas-Karvansarayi|title=Shah Abbas Caravanserai|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan - Ganja Regional Culture Office|language=en|archive-url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/monview/361/251/Sah-Abbas-Karvansarayi|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref> |- |Ughurlu khan caravanserai |XVII-XVIII centuries |Ughurlu khan karavanserai is located close to Shah Abbas karavanserai and dates back to the XVII-XVIII centuries. Traditional mixture of eggwhite with clay-lime and red brick was used in the construction. | |<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/monview/361/248/Ugurlu-Xan-karvansarayi|title=Ughurlu khan caravanserai|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan - Ganja Regional Culture Office|language=en|archive-url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/monview/361/248/Ugurlu-Xan-karvansarayi|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2017/09/04/m%C9%99d%C9%99niyy%C9%99t/'u%C4%9Furlu-xan'-karvansaras%C4%B1---xviii-%C9%99srin-yadigar%C4%B1-.html|title=Ughurlu khan caravanserai|last=|first=|date=|website=GanjaNews.az|language=az|archive-url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2017/09/04/m%C9%99d%C9%99niyy%C9%99t/'u%C4%9Furlu-xan'-karvansaras%C4%B1---xviii-%C9%99srin-yadigar%C4%B1-.html|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref> |}
== Mausoleums == {| class="wikitable" !Attraction !Period !Description !Picture !Citations |- |[[Nizami Mausoleum|Nizami Mausolem]] |1991 |Nizami Mausoleum is considered the symbol of Ganja. It is located in the entrance of Ganja in Ahmedli village on the east part of Ganja. The construction of the first Mausoleum on the grave of the outstanding poet [[Nizami Ganjavi]] dates back to the 13-14th centuries. The current structure of the monument was restored in 1991 on the existing building which was built in 1947. The garden around the tall cylindrical building constructed from solid granite blocks have statues inscribed on metal commemorating [[Nizami Ganjavi|Nizami]]'s epic poems. Recent restoration works in the Mausoleum transformed this garden into a campus on an area of 35 hectares which includes the Mausoleum, statues depicting scenes from [[Nizami Ganjavi|Nizami]]'s poems, artificial lake, 5 "[[Paisley (design)|buta]]" elements, and 5 fountains. |[[File:Gəncə - 20.07.17 - 21.jpg|center|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.azculture.az/nizami-g-nc-vinin-m-qb-r-kompleksi/|title=Nizami Ganjavi Mausoleum Complex|last=|first=|date=|website=Culture portal of the Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan|archive-url=http://www.azculture.az/nizami-g-nc-vinin-m-qb-r-kompleksi/|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref> |- |[[Tomb of Javad Khan|Tomb of Javad khan]] |2005 |The Tomb was eracted on the grave of the last ruler of Ganja Khanate Javad khan in 2005. Baked brick was used in the construction of this quadrangular-shaped tomb. It is located near the [[Juma Mosque, Ganja|Juma Mosque]]. |[[File:Chokak Bath and Javad khans tomb.JPG|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://heydar-aliyev-foundation.org/en/content/view/136/2208/Cavad-xan%C4%B1n-m%C9%99qb%C9%99r%C9%99si/|title=Javad Khan’s mausoleum|last=|first=|date=|website=heydar-aliyev-foundation.org|language=en|archive-url=https://heydar-aliyev-foundation.org/en/content/view/136/2208/Cavad-xan%C4%B1n-m%C9%99qb%C9%99r%C9%99si/|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2013/08/05/c%C9%99miyy%C9%99t/g%C9%99nc%C9%99nin-qeyr%C9%99t-r%C9%99mzi-%E2%80%93-cavad-xan-.html|title=Symbol of Ganja - Javad khan|last=|first=|date=|website=GanjaNews.az|language=az|archive-url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2013/08/05/c%C9%99miyy%C9%99t/g%C9%99nc%C9%99nin-qeyr%C9%99t-r%C9%99mzi-%E2%80%93-cavad-xan-.html|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref> |}
== Museums == {| class="wikitable" !Attraction !Period !Description !Picture !Citations |- |[[Nizami Ganjavi Ganja State History-Ethnography Museum|History-Ethnography Museum]] |1924 |[[Nizami Ganjavi Ganja State History-Ethnography Museum|The History-Ethnography Museum of Ganja]] is located at the back of Ganja City Hall in the former mansion of the descendants of [[Javad Khan|Javad khan]]. The museum was established in 1924 and moved to this building in 1972. The collection of the museum includes archaeological findings, ethnographic, epigraph, numismatic samples displayed in 18 rooms. A woman skeleton up to 220 cm high and accessories, as well as household items buried with her dated back to the 2nd millennium BC, Silver crown of [[Caucasian Albania]] era, lanterns discovered around [[Nizami Ganjavi]]'s grave, Ganja rugs, the flag of [[Ganja Khanate]], coins related to different periods of Azerbaijan history, jewelry, pottery, metalworking samples are among them. |[[File:Ganja History - Ethnography Museum building.jpg|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/53/NGencevi-adina-Gence-Dovlet-Tarix-Diyarsunasliq-Muzeyi|title=Ganja State History-Ethnography Museum|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan|language=|archive-url=http://www.ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/53/NGencevi-adina-Gence-Dovlet-Tarix-Diyarsunasliq-Muzeyi|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.anl.az/down/meqale/baki_xeber/2014/dekabr/411211.htm|title=History and Ethnography Museums|last=Sariyeva|first=Irada|date=16 May 2017|website=anl.az|language=Azerbaijani|archive-url=http://www.anl.az/down/meqale/baki_xeber/2014/dekabr/411211.htm|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.azculture.az/nizami-g-nc-vi-adina-g-nc-dovl-t-tarix-diyarsunasliq-muzeyi/|title=Ganja State History-Ethnography Museum|last=|first=|date=|website=Culture Portal of the Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan|archive-url=http://www.azculture.az/nizami-g-nc-vi-adina-g-nc-dovl-t-tarix-diyarsunasliq-muzeyi/|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://azertag.az/xeber/Gencedeki_tarix_diyarsunasliq_muzeyi_temir_edilecek-799181|title=History Museum in Ganja will be renovated|last=|first=|date=|work=Azerbaijan State News Agency|access-date=2018-09-24|archive-url=https://azertag.az/xeber/Gencedeki_tarix_diyarsunasliq_muzeyi_temir_edilecek-799181|archive-date=2018-09-24|language=az}}</ref><ref name="gencekitab">[https://www.gencekitab.az/docs/Muzey-tarix.doc Azərbaycan Respublikası Mədəniyyət və Turizm Nazirliyi Nizami Gəncəvi adına Gəncə Tarix-Diyarşünaslıq Muzeyi]</ref> |- |[[Nizami Ganjavi Ganja State History-Ethnography Museum#Ganja Fortress Gates|Ganja Fortress Gates Monumental Complex]] |2012-2014 |[[Nizami Ganjavi Ganja State History-Ethnography Museum#Ganja Fortress Gates|Monumental complex Ganja Fortress Gates - the Museum of Archaeology and Ethnography]] is located on the entrance to the eastern direction of [[Ganja, Azerbaijan|Ganja]] on the Baku-Gazakh highway. The complex was built between 2012-2014.The fortress was built on the both sides of the highway and its total length is 50 meters with bastions of 22 meters. The main 5-storey part of the fortress is considered 7-storey with the plinth. There is a State Flag installed in the park around the fortress. The underground tunnel, which is 62 meters long, connects the both fortresses. The complex includes 2 iron gates, a gallery of the portraits of outstanding figures from [[Ganja, Azerbaijan|Ganja]], Military History Museum of Ganja, ethnographic museum dedicated to the lifestyle and culture of the population Ganja in the Complex. The gates have been made on the sketches of ancient Ganja gates made by master Ibrahim Osmanoghlu in 1063 which were damaged in the result of 1139 Ganja earthquake and kept in [[Gelati Monastery]] of [[Kutaisi]] after [[Demetrius I of Georgia]] took it. |[[File:Ilham Aliyev reviewed the monumental complex Ganja Fortress Gates - the Museum of Archeology and Ethnography 19.jpg|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/59/Gence-Qala-Qapilari-%E2%80%93-Arxeologiya-ve-Etnoqrafiya--Muzeyi-Abide-Kompleksi|title=Monumental complex Ganja Fortress Gates - the Museum of Archaeology and Ethnography|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan - Ganja Regional Cultural Office|language=en|archive-url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/59/Gence-Qala-Qapilari-%E2%80%93-Arxeologiya-ve-Etnoqrafiya--Muzeyi-Abide-Kompleksi|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.president.az/articles/10855|title=Monumental complex Ganja Fortress Gates - the Museum of Archaeology and Ethnography|last=|first=|date=|website=en.president.az - Official web-site of President of Azerbaijan|language=en|archive-url=https://en.president.az/articles/10855|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref> |- |Nizami Ganjavi Museum |2014 |Nizami Museum located on the opposite site of [[Nizami Mausoleum]] was opened in 2014. There are exhibits reflecting the life and creativity of the poet, his manuscripts and illustrations on the motifs of “Khamsa”. There is a statue to the poet in front of the museum. |[[File:Ilham Aliyev attended the opening of the Museum of Nizami Ganjavi built in Ganja with support from the Heydar Aliyev Foundation.jpg|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/56/Gence-seher--Nizami-Gencevi-Muzeyi|title=Nizami Ganjavi Museum in Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan - Ganja Regional Culture Office|language=en|archive-url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/56/Gence-seher--Nizami-Gencevi-Muzeyi|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2017/07/08/m%C9%99d%C9%99niyy%C9%99t/nizami-g%C9%99nc%C9%99vi-muzeyi.html|title=Nizami Ganjavi Museum|last=|first=|date=|website=GanjaNews.az|language=az|archive-url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2017/07/08/m%C9%99d%C9%99niyy%C9%99t/nizami-g%C9%99nc%C9%99vi-muzeyi.html|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.president.az/articles/10853|title=Opening of the Museum of Nizami Ganjavi built in Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=en.president.az -Official web-site of President of Azerbaijan|language=en|archive-url=https://en.president.az/articles/10853|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref> |- |Mirza Shafi Vazeh Museum |2017 |The building of the museum located in Gulustan settlement of [[Ganja, Azerbaijan|Ganja]] was constructed between 2016 and 2017. The museum hosts an exhibition of documents and paintings related to the creativity of Azerbaijani poet and enlightener [[Mirza Shafi Vazeh]] who was born in Ganja in 1794. There is a special corner commemorating the literary society “Divan-i Hikmet” established by [[Mirza Shafi Vazeh|Vazeh]] in 1820. |[[File:Mirzə Şəfi Vazeh Muzeyi.jpg|frameless]] |<ref name=":3">{{Cite web|url=https://president.az/articles/25812|title=Inauguration of Mirza Shafi Vazeh Museum in Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=president.az - Official website of the President of Azerbaijan|language=az|archive-url=https://president.az/articles/25812|archive-date=2018-09-25|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-25}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{Cite web|url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/58/Gence-seher-Mirze-Sefi-Vazeh-Muzeyi|title=Mirza Shafi Vazeh museum in Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan - Ganja Regional Culture Office|language=en|archive-url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/58/Gence-seher-Mirze-Sefi-Vazeh-Muzeyi|archive-date=2018-09-25|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-25}}</ref> |- |Mir Jalal Pashayev house-museum |2007 |The house-museum of Azerbaijani writer [[Mir Jalal Pashayev]] who lived an worked in [[Ganja, Azerbaijan|Ganja]] was put into use in September 2007. | |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.azculture.az/g-nc-s-h-rind-mir-c-lal-pasayevin-ev-muzeyi/|title=House-museum of Mir Jalal Pashayev in Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=Culture portal of the Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan|archive-url=http://www.azculture.az/g-nc-s-h-rind-mir-c-lal-pasayevin-ev-muzeyi/|archive-date=2018-09-25|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/55/Gence-seher-Mir-Celal-Pasayev-Muzeyi|title=House-Museum of Mir Jalal Pashayev|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan - Ganja Regional Culture Office|language=|archive-url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/55/Gence-seher-Mir-Celal-Pasayev-Muzeyi|archive-date=2018-09-25|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-25}}</ref> |- |Museum of Miniature Books |2016 |Ganja branch of Museum of Miniature Books located City Hall Square of Ganja was inaugurated in 2016. It has a collection of more than a thousand miniature books. | |<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://azertag.az/xeber/Miniatur_Kitab_Muzeyinin_Gence_filiali_achilib-953694|title=Ganja branch of Miniature Books Museum opened in Ganja|last=|first=|date=|work=Azerbaijan State News Agency|access-date=2018-09-25|archive-url=https://azertag.az/xeber/Miniatur_Kitab_Muzeyinin_Gence_filiali_achilib-953694|archive-date=2018-09-25|language=az}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganja-ih.gov.az/news/381.html|title=Ganja branch of the Museum of Miniature Books opened in Heydar Aliyev square in Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=www.ganja-ih.gov.az - Official website of the Executive Power of Ganja|archive-url=http://www.ganja-ih.gov.az/news/381.html|archive-date=2018-09-25|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-25}}</ref> |}
== Parks and gardens == {| class="wikitable" !Attraction !Period !Description !Picture !Citations |- |[[Khan's Garden|Khan's garden]] |1847 |One of the main rest places of the population of Ganja was initially made as a garden of Javad khan on an area of 52 hectares during the [[Ganja Khanate]]. After Russian invasion, this garden was eradicated and some of the trees were relocated to newly established Sardar’s Garden by the [[Caucasus Viceroyalty (1801–1917)|viceroy of the Caucasus]] [[Mikhail Semyonovich Vorontsov]] on the lower part of previous garden in 1847. The garden was reconstructed after [[Azerbaijan]] gained independence and recalled “Khan’s garden”. There is a monument to the Azerbaijani poetess [[Nigar Rafibeyli]], tomb of [[Israfil Mammadov]], pine-tree alley, fountains, ponds, remains of [[Ganja Fortress|Ganja fortress]] walls and 350-seat open-air theater. |[[File:Khans garden in Ganja 2.JPG|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.president.az/articles/1547|title=Opening of the “Khan bagi” park of Ganja after its complete restoration|last=|first=|date=|website=en.president.az - Official web-site of President of Azerbaijan|language=en|archive-url=https://en.president.az/articles/1547|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Isayev|first=Ahmad|date=March 8, 2011|title=Khan's garden is the historical heritage|url=http://anl.az/down/meqale/azerbaycan/2011/mart/162130.htm|journal=Azerbaijan|volume=|pages=3|archive-url=http://anl.az/down/meqale/azerbaycan/2011/mart/162130.htm|archive-date=2018-09-24|via=National Library of Azerbaijan}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganja.az/az/m%C9%99d%C9%99niyy%C9%99t/parklar/329-xan-ba%C4%9F%C4%B1-m%C9%99d%C9%99niyy%C9%99t-v%C9%99-istirah%C9%99t-park%C4%B1|title=Khan's Garden|last=|first=|date=|website=Official website of Ganja city|language=az|archive-url=http://www.ganja.az/az/m%C9%99d%C9%99niyy%C9%99t/parklar/329-xan-ba%C4%9F%C4%B1-m%C9%99d%C9%99niyy%C9%99t-v%C9%99-istirah%C9%99t-park%C4%B1|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Mammadova|first=Hijran|date=2017-07-05|title=Travel to Ancient Ganja: Khan's garden|url=https://www.yenigence.com/q%C9%99dim-g%C9%99nc%C9%99y%C9%99-s%C9%99yah%C9%99t-xan-bagi/|journal=Yeni Ganja|volume=|pages=|archive-url=https://www.yenigence.com/q%C9%99dim-g%C9%99nc%C9%99y%C9%99-s%C9%99yah%C9%99t-xan-bagi/|archive-date=2018-09-24|via=}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite news|url=https://azertag.az/en/xeber/The_best_parks_in_regions_of_Azerbaijan___Mingachevir_Masalli_Ganja-1176047|title=The parks in regions of Azerbaijan - Mingachevir, Masalli, Ganja|last=|first=|date=|work=Azerbaijan State News Agency|access-date=2018-09-24|archive-url=https://azertag.az/en/xeber/The_best_parks_in_regions_of_Azerbaijan___Mingachevir_Masalli_Ganja-1176047|archive-date=2018-09-24|language=en}}</ref> |- |Heydar Aliyev park complex |2014 |Heydar Aliyev park complex covers an area of 450 hectares with 2 km length in Yeni Ganja residential area of [[Ganja, Azerbaijan|Ganja]]. It was inaugurated in 2014. The park complex includes 17 fountains and 32 decorated garden plots, an amphitheater for 3500 spectators, “Triumphal arch” with 40 meters height, Youth Center, Heydar Aliyev Center, Museum of Modern Art, a 4-step waterfall and an artificial lake on an area of 5 hectares. |[[File:Ilham Aliyev attended the opening of the Heydar Aliyev Park Complex and the Heydar Aliyev Center in Ganja 60.jpg|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.president.az/articles/10894|title=Opening of the Heydar Aliyev Park Complex and the Heydar Aliyev Center in Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=en.president.az - Official web-site of President of Azerbaijan|language=en|archive-url=https://en.president.az/articles/10894|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.yenigence.com/q%C9%99dim-g%C9%99nc%C9%99y%C9%99-s%C9%99yah%C9%99t-heyd%C9%99r-%C9%99liyev-adina-park-kompleks/|title=Heydar Aliyev Park Complex|last=|first=|date=2017-07-06|work=Yeni Gəncə|access-date=2018-09-24|archive-url=https://www.yenigence.com/q%C9%99dim-g%C9%99nc%C9%99y%C9%99-s%C9%99yah%C9%99t-heyd%C9%99r-%C9%99liyev-adina-park-kompleks/|archive-date=2018-09-24|language=az-AZ}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/76/Gence-seher-Heyder-Eliyev-adina-Park-Kompleksi|title=Heydar Aliyev Park Complex|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan - Ganja Regional Culture Office|language=en|archive-url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/76/Gence-seher-Heyder-Eliyev-adina-Park-Kompleksi|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref name=":2" /> |- |Ganjachay park-boulevard complex |2017 |The park-boulevard complex was opened along the bank of Ganjachay river in February 2017. The park is located on an area of 34 hectares with 1.2 km length. There are 15 fountains and 10 monuments installed in the park. The complex also includes Flag Square of Ganja, Ali and Nino Complex, Press House, bookstore, cafe and restaurants, playground and amusement facilities. |[[File:Ganjachay park-boulevard complex.jpg|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.president.az/articles/17813|title=President of Azerbaijan viewed Ganjachay park-boulevard complex|last=|first=|date=|website=en.president.az - Official web-site of President of Azerbaijan|language=en|archive-url=https://en.president.az/articles/17813|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/109/Gence-seher--Gencecay-park-bulvar-kompleksi|title=Ganjachay park-boulevard complex|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan - Ganja Regional Culture Office|language=en|archive-url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/109/Gence-seher--Gencecay-park-bulvar-kompleksi|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref> |- |Istiglal park |1991 |Istiglal park located in Gulustan settlement of [[Ganja, Azerbaijan|Ganja]] was opened on May 28, 1991 in honor to the [[Republic Day (Azerbaijan)|Republic day of Azerbaijan]]. There is a huge monument of [[Flag of Azerbaijan|Azerbaijani Flag]] and map. The park was renovated in 2014 and covers an area of 5 hectares. A monument in 15 meters high has been erected in honor to [[Azerbaijan Democratic Republic|ADR]] on which [[Declaration of Independence (Azerbaijan)|Declaration of Independence of Azerbaijan]] adopted on May 28, 1918 was inscribed. | |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/81/Gence-seher-Istiqlal-Xiyabani|title=Ganja Istiglal park|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan - Ganja Regional Culture Office|language=|archive-url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/81/Gence-seher-Istiqlal-Xiyabani|archive-date=2018-09-25|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://azertag.az/xeber/Azerbaycan_Xalq_Cumhuriyyetinin_96_ci_ildonumu_munasibetile_Gencede_Istiqlal_parki_istifadeye_verilmisdir-68193|title=Istiglal Park put into use in Ganja due to 96th anniversary of Azerbaijan Democratic Republic|last=|first=|date=|work=Azerbaijan State News Agency|access-date=2018-09-25|archive-url=https://azertag.az/xeber/Azerbaycan_Xalq_Cumhuriyyetinin_96_ci_ildonumu_munasibetile_Gencede_Istiqlal_parki_istifadeye_verilmisdir-68193|archive-date=2018-09-25|language=az}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2014/05/29/c%C9%99miyy%C9%99t/g%C9%99nc%C9%99d%C9%99-%E2%80%9Cistiqlal%E2%80%9D-park%C4%B1-istifad%C9%99y%C9%99-verilib.-fotolar.html?fb_comment_id=588465331261025_713214555452768#f15cdd65608b914|title=Istiglal park put into use in Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=GanjaNews.az|language=az|archive-url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2014/05/29/c%C9%99miyy%C9%99t/g%C9%99nc%C9%99d%C9%99-%E2%80%9Cistiqlal%E2%80%9D-park%C4%B1-istifad%C9%99y%C9%99-verilib.-fotolar.html?fb_comment_id=588465331261025_713214555452768#f15cdd65608b914|archive-date=2018-09-25|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-25}}</ref> |- |Mirza Shafi Vazeh park |2017 |The park named after [[Mirza Shafi Vazeh]] was built around Mirza Shafi Vazeh Museum in 2017. It is covering an area of 2 hectares. There is a statute to the outstanding Azerbaijani figure [[Mirza Shafi Vazeh|Vazeh]]. The wall behind the statue have been illustrated with the mosaic images of contemprories of [[Mirza Shafi Vazeh|Vazeh]]. |[[File:Mirza Shafi Vazeh park in Ganja, Azerbaijan.jpg|frameless]] |<ref name=":3" /><ref name=":4" /> |- |Nizami Ganjavi park in Hajikend |2018 |The Park named “The predecessors and successors of Nizami Ganjavi” was opened in [[Hacıkənd (Ganja)|Hajikend]] town in June 2018. There are a total of 17 monuments of prominent historical figures lived in Ganja, including [[Mahsati|Mahsati Ganjavi]], [[Mirza Shafi Vazeh]], Abul Ula Ganjavi, Givami Ganjavi, Usta Bender, Sheykh Zaman, Dokhtari Khatibi Ganjavi, Afrasiab, and Omar Ganji. The sculptor of the statues in the park is Asef Hasanov. |[[File:Park in Hajikend The predecessors and successors.jpg|frameless]] |<ref name=":02">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganja-ih.gov.az/news/599.html|title=The new building of the library was put into operation in Hajikend settlement of Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=Executive Power of Ganja|archive-url=http://www.ganja-ih.gov.az/news/599.html|archive-date=2018-09-25|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ganjanews.az/2018/06/21/c%C9%99miyy%C9%99t/g%C9%99nc%C9%99nin-hac%C4%B1k%C9%99nd-q%C9%99s%C9%99b%C9%99sind%C9%99-%E2%80%9Cnizami-g%C9%99nc%C9%99vi:-s%C9%99l%C9%99fl%C9%99r-v%C9%99-x%C9%99l%C9%99fl%C9%99r%E2%80%9D-muzeyi-yarad%C4%B1lacaq..html|title=Gəncənin Hacıkənd qəsəbəsində “Nizami Gəncəvi: Sələflər və xələflər” muzeyi yaradılacaq.|last=|first=|date=|website=GanjaNews.az|language=az|archive-url=http://ganjanews.az/2018/06/21/c%C9%99miyy%C9%99t/g%C9%99nc%C9%99nin-hac%C4%B1k%C9%99nd-q%C9%99s%C9%99b%C9%99sind%C9%99-%E2%80%9Cnizami-g%C9%99nc%