== Religious places == {| class="wikitable" !Attraction !Period !Description !Picture !Citations |- |[[Imamzadeh (Ganja)|Imamzadeh]] religious complex |XIV-XV centuries |[[Imamzadeh (Ganja)|Imamzadeh]] Complex – a pilgrimage site is located 7 kilometers northeast of [[Ganja, Azerbaijan|Ganja]]. The Complex includes Imamzadeh Mausoleum, Imamzadeh mosque, vault, caravanserai, cemetery and funerary monuments and surrounding brick walls with the entrance portal. The major monument of the complex is the Mausoleum which was constructed over the tomb of religious figure of the VIII century presumably in the XIV-XV centuries. The mosque, vault and other tombs were built in the XVII century. The height of the dome of the Mausoleum is 2.7 meters, while the Mausoleum has 12 meters height. The diameter of the dome covered with light-blue tiles is 4.4 meters. |[[File:İmamzadeh religious complex in Ganja.jpg|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.president.az/articles/1550|title=Construction-restoration works in “Imamzadeh” religious complex of Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=en.president.az - Official web-site of President of Azerbaijan|language=en|archive-url=https://en.president.az/articles/1550|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author = |editor= |format= |url= http://dic.academic.ru/dic.nsf/enc_pictures/1423/Кировабад |title= Кировабад |type= |origyear= | agency = Под ред. Полевого В. М. |edition= Популярная художественная энциклопедия |location= Мoscow |date= 1986 |year= 1986 |publisher= Soviet Encyclopedia |at= |volume= |issue= |number= |pages = |page= |series= |isbn = |issn = |doi = |bibcode = |arxiv = |pmid = |ref= |archiveurl = |archivedate = |language= |quote= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=http://anl.az/el/Kitab/2015/Azf-287414.pdf|title=Imamzadeh Mausoleum in Ganja|last=Hasanov|first=Elnur|last2=Azerbaijan National Academy of Sciences|publisher=Elm|year=2012|isbn=|location=Baku|pages=83-84}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=http://www.ebooks.azlibnet.az/book/yG3TDBJg.pdf|title=ИСТОРИЧЕСКИЙ ОЧЕРК ГОРОДА ГАНДЖИ|last=М. М. АЛЬТМАН|first=|publisher=|year=1949|isbn=|location=Baku|pages=21}}</ref> |- |[[Juma Mosque, Ganja|Juma Mosque]] |1606 |Juma Mosque is also called Shah Abbas Mosque because it was constructed during [[Abbas I of Persia|his reign]]. The mosque complex includes main mosque building, entrance portal with minarets on the both sides and former madrasa building. The Mosque building was built of red brick in 1606 and had its minarets added in 1776. The big white [[dome]] of the square-shaped mosque has a height of 17 meters. |[[File:Juma mosque in Ganja 3.jpg|center|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/monview/361/252/Cume-mescidi|title=Juma Mosque|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan - Ganja Regional Culture Office|language=az|archive-url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/monview/361/252/Cume-mescidi|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://scwra.gov.az/structure/183/?G%C9%99nc%C9%99%20%C5%9F%C9%99h%C9%99ri,%20%C5%9Eah%20Abbas%20m%C9%99scidi|title=Ganja, Shah Abbas mosque|last=|first=|date=|website=scwra.gov.az - official website of The State Committee on Religious Associations of the Republic of Azerbaijan|language=az|archive-url=http://scwra.gov.az/structure/183/?G%C9%99nc%C9%99%20%C5%9F%C9%99h%C9%99ri,%20%C5%9Eah%20Abbas%20m%C9%99scidi|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2013/07/26/c%C9%99miyy%C9%99t/xvii-%C9%99sr-az%C9%99rbaycan-memarl%C4%B1%C4%9F%C4%B1n%C4%B1n-%C5%9Fah-%C9%99s%C9%99ri---g%C9%99nc%C9%99--%C5%9Fah-abbas-m%C9%99scidi-.html|title=17th century Azerbaijani architecture - Ganja Shah Abbas Mosque|last=|first=|date=|website=GanjaNews.az|language=az|archive-url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2013/07/26/c%C9%99miyy%C9%99t/xvii-%C9%99sr-az%C9%99rbaycan-memarl%C4%B1%C4%9F%C4%B1n%C4%B1n-%C5%9Fah-%C9%99s%C9%99ri---g%C9%99nc%C9%99--%C5%9Fah-abbas-m%C9%99scidi-.html|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.az/books?id=un4WcfEASZwC&pg=RA1-PA85&lpg=RA1-PA85&dq=juma+mosque+ganja+dome&source=bl&ots=K905SdWYu7&sig=cJq5Yc_jT9BV2jwPWJ8--3U4Tc4&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwin3qb5i8LdAhWGqIsKHbdbD7c4FBDoATACegQIBxAB#v=onepage&q=juma%20mosque%20ganja%20dome&f=false|title=Grove Encyclopedia of Islamic Art & Architecture: Three-Volume Set|last=Jonathan Bloom, Sheila S. Blair, Sheila Blair|first=|publisher=OUP USA|year=2009|isbn=9780195309911|volume=2|location=New York|pages=85-86}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=Искусство Азербайджана|last=Aliyev|first=M|publisher=|year=1954|isbn=|volume=4|location=Baku|pages=664}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=Кировабад|last=Л. С. Бретеницкий, А. Саламзаде|first=|publisher=|year=1960|isbn=|location=|pages=39}}</ref> |- |[[Alexander Nevsky Church, Ganja|Alexander Nevsky Church]] |1887 |Alexander Nevsky Church is a Russian Orthodox church built in 1887 at the site of the old cemetery in Ganja during Russia’s occupation of Azerbaijan. The church building was built of bricks in the Byzantine architectural style. In the early years of USSR the functions of the Church discontinued and then reopened in 1946. Some icons in the interior have survived up to present as the icons of St. Alexander Nevsky and Mary Magdalene. |[[File:Alexander Nevsky church in Ganja 2018.jpg|frameless]] |<ref>[[Кишкинова, Евгения Михайловна|''Кишкинова Е. М.'']] «Византийское возрождение» в архитектуре России. Середина XIX — начало XX века. — СПб.: Искусство—СПБ, 2007. — 256 с. — {{ISBN|978-5-210-01611-9}}. — С. 248.</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://baku.eparhia.ru/church/al_nevskii/|title=Бакинско-Азербайджанская епархия РПЦ {{!}} Александро-Невский храм г.Гянджа|last=|first=|date=|website=baku.eparhia.ru|archive-url=http://baku.eparhia.ru/church/al_nevskii/|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.scwra.gov.az/structure/10/?%E2%80%9CAleksandr%20Nevski%E2%80%9D%20pravoslav%20kils%C9%99si|title=Aleksandr Nevski church|last=|first=|date=|website=www.scwra.gov.az - The State Committee on Religious Associations of the Republic of Azerbaijan|language=en|archive-url=http://www.scwra.gov.az/structure/10/?%E2%80%9CAleksandr%20Nevski%E2%80%9D%20pravoslav%20kils%C9%99si|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref> |}
== Cultural buildings == {| class="wikitable" !Attraction !Period !Description !Picture !Citations |- |[[Ganja State Philharmonic Hall|Ganja Philharmonic Hall]] |2017 |The new building of [[Ganja State Philharmonic Hall|Ganja Philharmonic Hall]] was inaugurated in 2017. It is located close to the central square of [[Ganja, Azerbaijan|Ganja]]. The balcony of the concert hall on the third floor features the statutes to the famous Azerbaijani composers [[Uzeyir Hajibeyov]], [[Fikret Amirov|Fikrat Amirov]], [[Gara Garayev]], [[Niyazi]] and [[Arif Malikov]]. |[[File:Ganja State Philharmonic Hall.jpg|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.president.az/articles/25806|title=Inauguration of the new building of Ganja State Philharmonic|last=|first=|date=|website=en.president.az - Official web-site of President of Azerbaijan|language=en|archive-url=https://en.president.az/articles/25806|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/52/Fikret-Emirov-adina-Gence-Dovlet-Filarmoniyasi|title=Ganja State Philharmonic Hall named after Fikrat Amirov|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan - Ganja Regional Culture Office|language=en|archive-url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/52/Fikret-Emirov-adina-Gence-Dovlet-Filarmoniyasi|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref> |- |[[Ganja State Puppet Theatre]] | |The building of the Ganja State Puppet Theater was constructed in 1885 as a Lutheran church by the German settlers moved to Elisabethpol (official name for Ganja in 1804–1918) after 1818. Tuff is the main material used its construction. |[[File:Gəncədə Lüteran kilsəsi.jpg|frameless|230x230px]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/50/Gence-Dovlet-Kukla-Teatri|title=Ganja State puppet Theatre|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan - Ganja Regional Cultural Office|language=|archive-url=http://www.ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/50/Gence-Dovlet-Kukla-Teatri|archive-date=2018-09-25|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-25}}</ref><ref name=":5" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.euronews.com/2015/04/27/german-footprints-in-the-caucasus|title=German footprints in the Caucasus|last=Pinna|first=Monica|date=27 April 2015|website=euronews.com|archive-url=http://www.euronews.com/2015/04/27/german-footprints-in-the-caucasus|archive-date=2018-09-25|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-25}}</ref> |- |Mahsati Ganjavi Center |2014 |It is a cultural center inaugurated in January 2014 commemorating poetess [[Mahsati|Mahsati Ganjavi]]. Photograph exhibition devoted to the creativity of the poetess, her poets, as well as a national garment exhibition related to the period when [[Mahsati]] lived are displayed in the Center. In addition, there is an exhibition of national musical instruments. The Center includes a statue to [[Mahsati|Mahsati Ganjavi]] and a park named after [[Mahsati|Mahsati Ganjavi]]. |[[File:Ilham Aliyev attended the opening of the Center of Mahsati Ganjavi built in Ganja with the support of the Heydar Aliyev Foundation 9.jpg|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://heydar-aliyev-foundation.org/en/content/view/136/3379/G%C9%99nc%C9%99d%C9%99-M%C9%99hs%C9%99ti-G%C9%99nc%C9%99vi-M%C9%99rk%C9%99zi/|title=Mahsati Ganjavi Centre in Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=heydar-aliyev-foundation.org|language=en|archive-url=https://heydar-aliyev-foundation.org/en/content/view/136/3379/G%C9%99nc%C9%99d%C9%99-M%C9%99hs%C9%99ti-G%C9%99nc%C9%99vi-M%C9%99rk%C9%99zi/|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://az.trend.az/azerbaijan/politics/2232518.html|title=Mahsati Ganjavi Center in Ganja was iaugurated|last=|first=|date=2014-01-22|work=Trend News agency|access-date=2018-09-24|archive-url=https://az.trend.az/azerbaijan/politics/2232518.html|archive-date=2018-09-24|language=az-AZ}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2017/06/10/c%C9%99miyy%C9%99t/g%C9%99nc%C9%99d%C9%99-g%C3%B6rm%C9%99li-oldu%C4%9Funuz-24-yer.html|title=24 attractions must seen in Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=GanjaNews.az|language=az|archive-url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2017/06/10/c%C9%99miyy%C9%99t/g%C9%99nc%C9%99d%C9%99-g%C3%B6rm%C9%99li-oldu%C4%9Funuz-24-yer.html|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/63/Gence-seher-Mehseti-Gencevi-Merkezi|title=Mahsati Ganjavi Center|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan - Ganja Regional Culture Office|language=en|archive-url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/view/360/63/Gence-seher-Mehseti-Gencevi-Merkezi|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.president.az/articles/10851|title=Opening of the Center of Mahsati Ganjavi built in Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=en.president.az -Official web-site of President of Azerbaijan|language=en|archive-url=https://en.president.az/articles/10851|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref> |}
== Squares == {| class="wikitable" !Attraction !Period !Description !Picture !Citations |- |Ganja City Hall Square |XX century |İt is the main square in Ganja called Heydar Aliyev square (former Lenin square). The building of Ganja Executive Power with tall arches and Heydar Aliyev Museum are located here. The building of Execute Power of Ganja was constructed during Soviet times in 1961 (architects E.İsmayilov and F.Leontyeva) and served as the administrative building of the City Committee of the [[Communist Party of the Soviet Union|CPSU]]. |[[File:Gəncə Şəhər İcra Hakimiyyəti.jpg|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.president.az/articles/4115|title=President Ilham Aliyev visited Ganja (2012)|last=|first=|date=|website=en.president.az - Official web-site of President of Azerbaijan|language=en|archive-url=https://en.president.az/articles/4115|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=http://modernlib.net/books/bse/bolshaya_sovetskaya_enciklopediya_ki/read_34/|title=Great Soviet Encyclopedia (K-İ) - Kirovabad|last=|first=|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=34}}</ref> |- |Flag square |2012 |The Flag Square of Ganja is a large city square located on the right bank of Ganja river. A flag measuring 50 by 25 flies on a pole 100 m high. The Flag square of Ganja was inaugurated on 21 January 2012. |[[File:Flag square in Ganja, Azerbaijan.jpg|frameless|212x212px]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.president.az/articles/4121|title=Flag square of Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=en.president.az - Official web-site of President of Azerbaijan|language=en|archive-url=https://en.president.az/articles/4121|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2014/11/09/iqtisadiyyat/g%C9%99nc%C9%99nin-bayraq-meydan%C4%B1.html|title=Flag Square of Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=GanjaNews.az|language=az|archive-url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2014/11/09/iqtisadiyyat/g%C9%99nc%C9%99nin-bayraq-meydan%C4%B1.html|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref> |}
== Shopping == {| class="wikitable" |- !Attraction !Period !Description !Picture !Citations |- |Javad khan street | |Javad Khan Street is the traditional large pedestrian and shopping street that is located in the downtown Ganja. The most of the buildings along the street date back to Russian Empire period of Ganja history. |[[File:Cavad Xan-1.JPG|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2014/01/13/c%C9%99miyy%C9%99t/g%C9%99nc%C9%99nin-cavad-xan-k%C3%BC%C3%A7%C9%99si.html|title=Javad khan street in Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=GanjaNews.az|language=az|archive-url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2014/01/13/c%C9%99miyy%C9%99t/g%C9%99nc%C9%99nin-cavad-xan-k%C3%BC%C3%A7%C9%99si.html|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref> |- |Ganja Mall |2014-2017 |Constructed between 2014 and 2017, Ganja Mall is considered as the city's largest mall. 8-storey mall has a total area of 26.293 square meters. |[[File:Ganja-mall.jpg|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ganjanews.az/2017/11/22/iqtisadiyyat/%E2%80%9Cg%C9%99nc%C9%99-mall%E2%80%9D-ticar%C9%99t-m%C9%99rk%C9%99zi.html|title=Ganja Mall|last=|first=|date=|website=GanjaNews.az|language=az|archive-url=http://ganjanews.az/2017/11/22/iqtisadiyyat/%E2%80%9Cg%C9%99nc%C9%99-mall%E2%80%9D-ticar%C9%99t-m%C9%99rk%C9%99zi.html|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref name=":12">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganja-ih.gov.az/page/10.html|title=About the city|last=|first=|date=|website=Executive Power of Ganja|archive-url=http://www.ganja-ih.gov.az/page/10.html|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://worldarchitecture.org/architecture-projects/hpfcz/ganja_mall-project-pages.html|title=Ganja Mall|last=|first=|date=|website=worldarchitecture.org|language=en|archive-url=https://worldarchitecture.org/architecture-projects/hpfcz/ganja_mall-project-pages.html|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web