== Nature == {| class="wikitable" !Attraction !Period !Description !Picture !Citations |- |[[Hacıkənd (Ganja)|Hajikend]] village | |[[Hacıkənd (Ganja)|Hajikend]] is the major resort zone for people of [[Ganja, Azerbaijan|Ganja]] and surrounding areas in the administrative-territorial unit of [[Kapaz raion]] of [[Ganja, Azerbaijan|Ganja]]. It is situated 23 km south of Ganja, on the north-eastern of the [[Lesser Caucasus]] mountains. |[[File:Hacikend.jpg|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://azertag.az/en/xeber/Collection_of_beautiful_lakes_of_Azerbaijan-1147159|title=Collection of beautiful lakes of Azerbaijan|last=|first=|date=|work=Azerbaijan State News Agency|access-date=2018-09-25|archive-url=https://azertag.az/en/xeber/Collection_of_beautiful_lakes_of_Azerbaijan-1147159|archive-date=2018-09-25|language=en}}</ref><ref name=":02" /> |}
== Others == {| class="wikitable" !Attraction !Period !Description !Picture !Citations |- |Khamsa Monumental Compound |2016 |Khamsa Monumental Compound consists of 5 large book-shaped monuments recalling Nizami’s poems in the park line along the highway between Ganja fortress gates and [[Nizami Mausoleum]]. Each of them has 12 meters length, 9 meters height and 2 meter width. The book-shaped monuments have different colors: "[[Nizami Ganjavi#Makhzan al-Asrar|The Treasury of Mysteries]]" is black symbolizing keeping secrets,
"[[Khosrow and Shirin|Khosrov and Shirin]]" is golden symbolizing throne, "[[Layla and Majnun]]" is white symbolizing pure love, [[The Seven Beauties (poem)|"The Seven Beauties]]" is turquoise symbolizing kings’ talisman in the East, and "[[Nizami Ganjavi#Eskandar Nameh|Romance of Alexander the Great]]" is red symbolizing victory. |[[File:Ilham Aliyev reviewed the monumental complex Ganja Fortress Gates - the Museum of Archeology and Ethnography 17.jpg|frameless]] |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.president.az/articles/4125|title=Construction of Gala Compound in Ganja|last=|first=|date=|website=en.president.az - Official web-site of President of Azerbaijan|language=en|archive-url=https://en.president.az/articles/4125|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2017/06/07/m%C9%99d%C9%99niyy%C9%99t/%E2%80%9Cx%C9%99ms%C9%99%E2%80%9D-abid%C9%99-kompleksi-nadir-s%C9%99n%C9%99t-incisidir.html|title=Khamsa Monumental Compound|last=|first=|date=|website=GanjaNews.az|language=az|archive-url=http://www.ganjanews.az/2017/06/07/m%C9%99d%C9%99niyy%C9%99t/%E2%80%9Cx%C9%99ms%C9%99%E2%80%9D-abid%C9%99-kompleksi-nadir-s%C9%99n%C9%99t-incisidir.html|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Muradov|first=Zakir|date=2016-10-10|title=Ganja, Nizami's birthplace|url=https://525.az/site/?name=xeberprint&kecid=1&news_id=65568|journal=525|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref> |- |[[Bottle house of Ganja|Bottle House]] |1966-1967 |Bottle house is a private residence built entirely out of glass bottles and colorful stones in 1966-1967 by a resident of [[Ganja, Azerbaijan|Ganja]]. The house was dedicated to the memory of the brother who went missing during World War II. The walls of the house were decorated with the portraits of family members and their names, construction year of the house and “Ganja” inscriptions. |[[File:Bottle House in Ganja.jpg|frameless]] |<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/city/30|title=Ganja city|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan - Ganja Regional Culture Office|language=Azerbaijani|archive-url=http://ganja.mctgov.az/az/city/30|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref><ref name=":5">{{Cite web|url=http://www.anl.az/down/meqale/525/2010/may/120827.htm|title=Ganja in liberty history:A review to the struggle for the restoration of ancient and glorious name|last=Boran Aziz|first=|date=|website=National Library of Azerbaijan|language=Azerbaijani|archive-url=http://www.anl.az/down/meqale/525/2010/may/120827.htm|archive-date=2018-09-24|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-24}}</ref> |}
== Places nearby == {| class="wikitable" |+ !Attraction !Period !Description !Picture !Citations |- |[[Göygöl National Park|Goygol national Park]] |2008 |[[Göygöl National Park|Goygol National Park]] was founded in April, 2008 on the base of Goygol State Nature Reserve established in 1925, in the territories of administrative raions of Goygol, [[Goranboy District|Goranboy]] and [[Dashkasan District|Dashkasan]]. [[Göygöl National Park|Goygol National Park]] is located at an altitude between 1100 and 3065 meters. |[[File:Göygöl Milli Parkı (5).jpg|frameless|182x182px]] |<ref name=":42">{{Cite web|url=http://eco.gov.az/en/660-goygyol-national-park|title=Goygol National Park|last=|first=|date=|website=eco.gov.az|language=en|archive-url=http://eco.gov.az/en/660-goygyol-national-park|archive-date=2018-08-28|dead-url=|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref><ref name=":13">{{Cite web|url=http://www.goygol-ih.gov.az/page/13.html|title=Location|last=|first=|date=|website=Executive Power of Goygol|archive-url=http://www.goygol-ih.gov.az/page/13.html|archive-date=2018-08-28|dead-url=|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref> |- |[[Lake Göygöl|Lake Goygol]] | |[[Lake Göygöl|Goygol]] ([[Azerbaijani language|Azerbaijani]]: ''Göygöl'', literally "the Blue Lake") is a natural impounded lake in [[Azerbaijan]]. It is situated at the footsteps of [[Murovdag]] at an altitude of 1556 meters not far from [[Ganja, Azerbaijan|Ganja]]. |[[File:Geygol.jpg|frameless]] |<ref name=":15">{{Cite web|url=http://www.goygol-ih.gov.az/page/13.html|title=Location|last=|first=|date=|website=Executive Power of Goygol|archive-url=http://www.goygol-ih.gov.az/page/13.html|archive-date=2018-08-28|dead-url=|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref><ref>[http://oval.ru/enc/17152.html Большая Советская Энциклопедия: Гейгель]</ref> |- |[[Maral-gol|Lake Maralgol]] | |Maralgol is a mountainous lake at the height of 1910 m. on [[Murovdag]] Mountain in the west of [[Azerbaijan]]. The lake occupies the territory of 23 hectares with utmost depth of 60 m. |[[File:Maralgol Lake 0.jpg|frameless]] |<ref name=":15" /> |}
